B. verticillata has many other designations by which it is referred to globally as shown in 
Table 1. This plant species is popularly called whitehead broom, southern larra flower and shrubby false buttonwood in English language. In West Africa countries, different tribes and ethnic groups have their unique names for this weed (
Abdullahi-Gero et al., 2014; 
Andrioli et al., 2014; 
Campos et al., 2014).
